---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Eyebrow from '../components/Eyebrow.astro';
import DataFigure from '../components/DataFigure.astro';
import SourceList from '../components/SourceList.astro';
import TonnageBars from '../components/charts/TonnageBars.astro';
import TruckMath from '../components/charts/TruckMath.astro';
import CumulativeDeposit from '../components/charts/CumulativeDeposit.astro';
import HierarchyFunnel from '../components/charts/HierarchyFunnel.astro';
import LinerLife from '../components/charts/LinerLife.astro';

const sources = [
  {
    title: 'Proposed Blakebrook tonnage and 50-year life',
    publisher: 'Lismore City Council / Lismore App',
    note: '60,000 t/yr figure. URL to verify.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Metro landfill reference (~200,000+ t/yr)',
    publisher: 'Mayor Steve Krieg public statement',
    date: 'September 2025',
  },
  {
    title: 'R. Kerry Rowe — HDPE geomembrane service life vs temperature',
    publisher: 'Peer-reviewed geoenvironmental engineering literature',
    date: '2020',
    note: 'Anchor: ~54 years at 60°C. Full citation on the sources page.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The numbers"
  description="Five hand-built data visualisations: tonnage compared, the real truck math, 50-year cumulative deposit, the waste hierarchy as a funnel, and how liner service life depends on temperature."
  progress
  article
>
  <header class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 pt-14 sm:pt-20">
    <Eyebrow>The numbers</Eyebrow>
    <h1
      class="mt-4 max-w-[16ch] font-display text-4xl font-extrabold leading-[1.04] tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink sm:text-6xl"
    >
      Five figures worth doing carefully
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-soft">
      Numbers settle some arguments and reframe others. Each figure shows its
      working and its source. Where a value is approximate, we say so on the
      chart rather than imply false precision.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 pb-8">
    <div class="fig-row">
      <div class="fig-text prose-body">
        <h2>1. Tonnage compared to capacity</h2>
        <p>
          The public case leans on a tonnage comparison: 60,000 t/yr here versus
          200,000+ t/yr at metro landfills. The figure shows that contrast — but
          the point is its caption. Tonnage is the wrong yardstick; what matters
          is the receiving environment.
        </p>
      </div>
      <DataFigure
        caption="Approximate annual tonnages (illustrative)"
        source="Blakebrook 60 kt is the proposed figure; Lucas Heights ~200 kt is the metro reference used in the public debate. Regional figures marked * are approximate and to be verified. The comparison is illustrative — a smaller tonnage in a sensitive, high-rainfall catchment can carry more risk than a larger tonnage on an arid, deep-watertable site."
      >
        <TonnageBars />
      </DataFigure>
    </div>

    <div class="fig-row">
      <div class="fig-text prose-body">
        <h2>2. The truck math</h2>
        <p>
          &ldquo;400 trucks a day&rdquo; is dismissed as hype; the honest answer
          is neither 400 nor zero. The arithmetic is simple, and so is the
          conclusion: a real, assessable increase in local traffic.
        </p>
      </div>
      <DataFigure
        caption="From annual tonnage to daily gate movements"
        source="60,000 t ÷ ~250 operating days ÷ ~18 t average payload ≈ 13 inbound loads/day. Adding empty returns, cover-soil, leachate tankers and staff gives ~40 movements/day. Segment values are illustrative, not a traffic study."
      >
        <TruckMath />
      </DataFigure>
    </div>

    <div class="fig-row">
      <div class="fig-text prose-body">
        <h2>3. Cumulative deposit over 50 years</h2>
        <p>
          A 50-year facility is not a 60,000-tonne decision. It is a
          one-to-three million tonne decision, accumulating in one location.
        </p>
      </div>
      <DataFigure
        caption="Cumulative tonnes deposited, year 0 to year 50"
        source="Upper line: a flat 60 kt/yr → ~3.0 Mt. Lower dashed line: a long-run average of ~36 kt/yr → ~1.8 Mt. The band is the range implied by different volume-growth assumptions."
      >
        <CumulativeDeposit />
      </DataFigure>
    </div>

    <div class="fig-row">
      <div class="fig-text prose-body">
        <h2>4. The waste hierarchy as a funnel</h2>
        <p>
          The size of the hole you need depends entirely on how much waste you
          let reach the bottom of the funnel. Closing the diversion gap is the
          cheapest capacity you can build.
        </p>
      </div>
      <DataFigure
        caption="What reaches landfill under different diversion rates"
        source="At today's roughly 60% diversion, about 40% of the stream is landfilled. At a 90% target, about 10% is. FOGO recovery rates across Northern Rivers LGAs vary widely, so the gap is real and addressable."
      >
        <HierarchyFunnel />
      </DataFigure>
    </div>

    <div class="fig-row">
      <div class="fig-text prose-body">
        <h2>5. Liner service life vs temperature</h2>
        <p>
          &ldquo;The liner protects the groundwater&rdquo; is true within an
          envelope. That envelope is set by temperature and leachate chemistry —
          and it is steep.
        </p>
      </div>
      <DataFigure
        caption="HDPE geomembrane service life falls steeply with temperature"
        source="Illustrative curve; magnitudes follow the ranges in Rowe (2020) — roughly 54 years at 60°C, rising to several hundred years at lower temperatures. Shaded band is a typical liner operating range."
      >
        <LinerLife />
      </DataFigure>
    </div>

    <SourceList sources={sources} />
  </div>

  <style>
    .fig-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.82fr) minmax(0, 1.18fr);
      gap: 44px;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 12px 0;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    }
    .fig-row:first-of-type {
      border-top: 0;
    }
    .fig-text h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .fig-row :global(figure) {
      margin-top: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 24px;
      width: 100%;
    }
    @media (max-width: 860px) {
      .fig-row {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 4px;
      }
      .fig-row :global(figure) {
        margin-top: 12px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
